Ahead of the 2023 general elections, the Senior Special Assistant to the Delta State Governor on Peace and Conflict Resolution, Olorogun Samson Gorsons, has tendered his resignation to Governor Arthur Ifeanyi Okowa. This is to enable him pursue his political ambition into the Delta State House of Assembly in Ughelli South Constituency. Olorogun tendered his resignation through the Secretary to the State Government, Patrick Ukah. While thanking the governor for the opportunity given to him to serve, Olorogun said the reason for his resignation was to allow him pursue and achieve his political ambition.